217
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:46,390
[Horn conch porridge]

218
00:17:44,990 --> 00:17:46,830
like if she has any friends or family.

219
00:17:49,830 --> 00:17:52,670
But why are you looking for her?

220
00:17:52,830 --> 00:17:54,570
She's close to a friend of mine,

221
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,040
and I have some business with her.

222
00:17:56,370 --> 00:17:58,040
Anyway, thank you.

223
00:17:59,370 --> 00:18:03,540
[Horn conch porridge, 12,000 won]

224
00:18:06,580 --> 00:18:08,850
Where on earth did she go?

225
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:12,350
I haven't seen her ever since the funeral.

226
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:15,060
She's probably fine.

227
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:17,190
She couldn't have gone far either.

228
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:19,990
Jeju Island isn't that big anyway.

229
00:18:20,230 --> 00:18:22,600
But I'm worried something
might've happened--

230
00:18:22,660 --> 00:18:26,070
Come on. You're prohibited
from thinking useless things.

231
00:18:27,230 --> 00:18:29,500
I'll look for Ms. Sim Ae-soon more,

232
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:32,340
so let's wrap it up for today

233
00:18:32,410 --> 00:18:34,010
and go get something to eat.

234
00:18:34,070 --> 00:18:35,540
